1
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:12,500
[FEMALE DJ] Welcome back,
we hope everyone's enjoying

2
00:00:12,583 --> 00:00:14,125
this spectacular Sunday.

3
00:00:14,208 --> 00:00:17,083
And speaking of spectacular,
there's a fireworks festival

4
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:18,791
going on
in Higashi-cho later today.

5
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:20,875
[FUTARO]
I've got a whole day to myself.

6
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,541
That means I can forget
the brats

7
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:24,333
and study to my heart's content!

8
00:00:24,416 --> 00:00:26,166
[DJ continues indistinct]

9
00:00:26,250 --> 00:00:27,416
Wait a second.

10
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,625
I should teach them
this formula here.

11
00:00:29,708 --> 00:00:31,833
They could all solve
this problem,

12
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:33,166
even Yotsuba.

13
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:35,083
Ohh! One for Miku!

14
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:37,875
Uh...

15
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:39,666
What the hell am I doing?

16
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:43,291
Ugh! Why do I care
about that stuff?

17
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:44,791
-[doorbell rings]
-Huh?

18
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:47,041
Must be a loan shark.

19
00:00:48,291 --> 00:00:50,250
Sorry, we can't pay it right...

20
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,500
now.

21
00:00:52,583 --> 00:00:56,000
♪

22
00:00:56,083 --> 00:00:57,208
[knocking on door]

23
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:58,791
[ITSUKI]
Don't shut the door on me!

24
00:00:58,875 --> 00:00:59,958
Open up!

25
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:03,541
Hello?

26
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:06,708
I'll be quick.
I just have something for you.

27
00:01:08,208 --> 00:01:11,041
My father left your pay,
so I came to drop it off.

28
00:01:13,458 --> 00:01:16,125
[RAIHA] Stop shaking.
You're crumpling Yukichi's face!

29
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,791
You get five thousand yen
a day for each of us.

30
00:01:19,875 --> 00:01:22,208
For two days,
that's fifty-thousand yen.

31
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:26,166
[RAIHA] Look, Mama,
he's not useless after all!

32
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:29,458
[FUTARO] At this rate,
we'll be debt-free in no time!

33
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,416
Well, that's all
I came here for.

34
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,916
[FUTARO]
I can't take this.

35
00:01:36,916 --> 00:01:38,333
[RAIHA]
Huh?

36
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:40,500
It's true that I went there
twice with the intent

37
00:01:40,583 --> 00:01:41,666
to tutor you girls.

38
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:43,541
But I didn't do anything.

39
00:01:45,958 --> 00:01:47,500
Oh, I wouldn't say that.

40
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,291
You did make a move
on my sister.

41
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:50,500
Wait, you did what?

42
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:52,125
[FUTARO]
I thought we adjudicated that!

43
00:01:52,208 --> 00:01:54,750
[ITSUKI] Either way,
you haven't done nothing.

44
00:01:57,208 --> 00:01:58,708
Having you at our house,

45
00:01:58,791 --> 00:02:01,625
It's beginning to change
something within the five of us.

46
00:02:02,875 --> 00:02:04,833
-Five?
-[ITSUKI] Uhh!

47
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,833
Uh... No, I meant those four.

48
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,791
Anyway, I'm not going
to accept this money back,

49
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:12,625
so you might as well keep it and
do whatever you please with it.

50
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:17,166
[groaning]

51
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:21,375
Hey, Raiha. Is there anything
you've been wanting?

52
00:02:21,458 --> 00:02:22,666
[beeping]

53
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,625
[coins clinking]

54
00:02:25,708 --> 00:02:28,166
Aaah!

55
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:31,041
Hey, Big Brother! Check it out.
I won the big jackpot!

56
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:33,791
[laughs]
Yeah, that's cool!

57
00:02:33,875 --> 00:02:35,625
Still don't see
why you're here, though.

58
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:37,000
Look, I didn't have a choice.

59
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:40,500
I know! You can take me
out to the arcade!

60
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,708
But I want you to come
with us, too, Itsuki.

61
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:45,000
Will you?

62
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,625
You could've said no!

63
00:02:47,708 --> 00:02:50,125
No, I couldn't!
She's way too darn cute!

64
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:51,208
I know!

65
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:53,125
[FUTARO]
Bring it on!

66
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:54,833
[RAIHA]
Gotcha!

67
00:02:54,916 --> 00:02:56,625
[BOTH giggling]

68
00:02:58,541 --> 00:03:00,666
-[RAIHA] Whoa!
-[FUTARO] Ugh!

69
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:02,000
-[RAIHA] Over here.
-[FUTARO] It's rigged.

70
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:03,666
-[RAIHA giggling]
-[ITSUKI] Uh?

71
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:06,666
[laughing]

72
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,750
♪

73
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:12,666
Huh?

74
00:03:14,958 --> 00:03:17,583
Raiha's really enjoying herself.

75
00:03:17,666 --> 00:03:19,000
It's tough for her, you know,

76
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:21,416
because of our family's
debt situation.

77
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:24,875
I assume there's a whole list
of things she'd like to do.

78
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:28,000
That's why I want to make
all her wishes come true.

79
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,333
Ahhh!

80
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,708
Big Brother, Itsuki, look!

81
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:34,666
Can the three of us do that
before we go home?

82
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:38,125
♪

83
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:42,250
I don't know, that game
over there looks way better.

84
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:48,291
You said "all of her wishes."

85
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,375
Come on.

86
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:52,625
[FUTARO] On second thought,
I'll pass.

87
00:03:52,708 --> 00:03:55,333
[RAIHA] Nice try, bro.
You ready, Itsuki?

88
00:03:55,416 --> 00:03:56,500
[ITSUKI]
Uh, yeah.

89
00:03:57,541 --> 00:04:01,166
Isn't this awesome?
It's just like a family photo!

90
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,708
-Is it?
-Is it?

91
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:04,041
[camera shutter clicks]

92
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:06,000
♪

93
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:08,500
What is going on
with your expression?

94
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:10,250
You look worse.

95
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,416
I love it!

96
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,791
Thanks a lot, both of you!

97
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,500
I'll cherish this thing forever!

98
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:19,541
♪

99
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,125
[RAIHA humming]

100
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:28,291
So much for spending
my precious Sunday on studying.

101
00:04:28,375 --> 00:04:30,375
Well, I still have the evening.

102
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:33,125
You quintuplets had better
hit the books tonight too.

103
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:34,625
Eeh!

104
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:37,125
Wow, would you look at the time!

105
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,000
Okay, I'm suspicious!

106
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:40,166
I know you had homework.

107
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,666
Don't tell me
you haven't done it!

108
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:44,208
Go away! Stop following me!

109
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:47,458
Hey, Big Brother?
I see four Itsukis.

110
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,000
Huh? Uh!

111
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,875
Hey, look, it's Uesugi!

112
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:57,125
What's Itsuki doing
with that waste of space?

113
00:04:57,208 --> 00:05:00,333
Ooh, were you two out
on a date? Our bad.

114
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:01,583
[ITSUKI]
Of course we're not!

115
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:03,500
Aww, hi!

116
00:05:03,583 --> 00:05:05,625
You must be
Uesugi's little sister!

117
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:06,583
Uh-huh.

118
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,000
You know what?

119
00:05:08,083 --> 00:05:10,500
You should come see
the fireworks with us!

120
00:05:10,583 --> 00:05:12,000
Wow, really?

121
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,458
Wait a second.

122
00:05:13,541 --> 00:05:15,708
I already made plans
to study today.

123
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:17,416
And you guys have homework!

124
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:18,416
[ALL gasp]

125
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,916
Pretty please?

126
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:22,083
Can we?

127
00:05:25,125 --> 00:05:26,541
Well, of course we can.

128
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:27,958
But only...

129
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:29,666
-[whimpering]
-[FUTARO] ...after...

130
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:31,125
all of you...

131
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:32,833
are done with...

132
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:33,875
your work!

133
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,666
[cries]

134
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:40,208
We'll never finish in time
for the fireworks show!

135
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,583
[CROWD murmuring excitedly]

136
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:16,833
♪

137
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,458
[NINO] We made it!
[laughs]

138
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:23,500
[RAIHA]
Good work, everybody!

139
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,375
[YOTSUBA] When are the fireworks
supposed to start?

140
00:07:25,458 --> 00:07:27,500
[ITSUKI]
They're from 7:00 to 8:00.

141
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:29,666
[ICHIKA] I'm gonna go
check out the stalls!

142
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,625
[FUTARO] What are they
so enthusiastic about?

143
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:38,416
Ooh! Wanna try
to catch a goldfish?

144
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,333
Sure!

145
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:40,625
-Yay!
-Yay!

146
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:42,500
♪

147
00:07:42,583 --> 00:07:43,875
[FUTARO sighs]

148
00:07:45,125 --> 00:07:48,000
Well, either way,
at least they actually did

149
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,875
their homework
for once in their lives.

150
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,833
They must've really wanted
to see the fireworks.

151
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:55,416
[ITSUKI]
Why the long face?

152
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,166
Lighten up, we're at a festival!

153
00:07:57,250 --> 00:08:01,166
♪

154
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,208
Whoa!

155
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:06,833
Would you please stop
staring at me?

156
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:09,333
-[FUTARO] Oh, great.
-Huh?

157
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:12,041
The five of you are hard enough
to tell apart as it is.

158
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,875
Don't go changing
your hairstyle.

159
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,333
Ugh, I'm Itsuki!

160
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:18,625
And I'll do it the way I want!
It's on my head!

161
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:20,250
Come on now.

162
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,833
That just won't do.

163
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:24,166
When a girl changes her hair...

164
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,041
you should compliment her.

165
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:28,875
I know.

166
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:31,708
Wanna find out if girls really
do wear yukata with no undies?

167
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:34,666
That's not the norm anymore.
Don't bother.

168
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,458
Well, there's only one way
to be sure.

169
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,041
♪

170
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:41,416
Ichika, whoa!

171
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:44,083
I'm just messing with you.

172
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:46,416
-Ugh.
-Admit it.

173
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:47,916
I had you going there!

174
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,833
[cell phone buzzing]

175
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:54,000
Hey, why are you all
standing around wasting time?

176
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:56,416
Ichika, time to go.

177
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,750
Uh, sorry. Phone call! Yes.

178
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,416
Tonight, really?

179
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:04,666
Hmm?

180
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:05,958
[NINO]
And you!

181
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:09,500
It should've only been
the five of us.

182
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:11,708
So why are you tagging along?

183
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:14,541
Look, I just came here
for my little sister.

184
00:09:14,625 --> 00:09:16,083
[RAIHA]
Big Brother!

185
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:17,416
Look what I got!

186
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:20,583
Yotsuba caught some fish for me!

187
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:23,333
♪

188
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,750
Don't you think
that many fish is overkill?

189
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:29,541
Well, I saw her looking up at me
with that adorable face

190
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,875
and I just couldn't resist!

191
00:09:31,958 --> 00:09:34,250
And look at what else
she bought me!

192
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:36,375
[FUTARO] That's the last thing
we need today!

193
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:39,583
[RAIHA] Sorry, I couldn't wait
for the show.

194
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,625
Well, that was nice
of her, I guess.

195
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,125
Did you say thank you?

196
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:47,750
Thanks a lot, Yotsuba!
I love you!

197
00:09:49,541 --> 00:09:52,208
Oh, my goodness, you are so
precious, you don't even know.

198
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:54,458
I wish you could be
my younger sister too!

199
00:09:54,541 --> 00:09:56,791
Hang on, I just realized.

200
00:09:56,875 --> 00:09:59,625
All I would have to do is get
hitched with Uesugi one day.

201
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:02,375
Then we really
would become sisters.

202
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:05,000
Do you have any idea
how stupid you sound right now?

203
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,458
And don't you get any ideas
about Yotsuba, mister!

204
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:09,875
I won't!

205
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:12,833
Sorry!

206
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:14,375
It's fine.

207
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:17,208
I'm back!

208
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:19,166
Well, shall we?

209
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:22,791
Hmm? Are you going somewhere?

210
00:10:22,875 --> 00:10:25,958
Nino rented out the roof
of one of the shops for us.

211
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:28,791
The whole roof? Rich people!

212
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,541
Hold on, we can't go yet.

213
00:10:31,625 --> 00:10:32,833
[ALL]
Huh?

214
00:10:32,916 --> 00:10:34,208
[NINO] Did we really come
to a festival

215
00:10:34,291 --> 00:10:36,375
and forget to buy
that one thing?

216
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:37,708
[ALL gasp]

217
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,625
[MIKU] She's right,
we haven't bought it.

218
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:41,250
[ICHIKA]
We almost forgot!

219
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:42,958
[ITSUKI] Do they have it
at one of the stalls?

220
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,875
[YOTSUBA]
Ooh, I can't wait to get it!

221
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:47,375
Do I want to know?

222
00:10:47,458 --> 00:10:48,750
[QUINTUPLETS]
All together.

223
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,416
[overlapping chatter]

224
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,250
[FUTARO groans]

225
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,250
[QUINTUPLETS]
Let's go buy the thing!

226
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:58,208
For a set
of identical quintuplets,

227
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:00,041
you sure are different.

228
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:03,375
[CROWD chattering]

229
00:11:03,458 --> 00:11:04,958
Stay close.

230
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:07,250
I don't want you
getting lost, okay?

231
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,375
Hold my sleeve.

232
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:09,708
[RAIHA]
'Kay!

233
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:14,666
Ugh, that salesman
was the worst!

234
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,208
Man, what a jerk.

235
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:18,791
[MAN] How about a freebie
for the pretty young lady?

236
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:23,583
So why didn't he give me any?
I look just like you!

237
00:11:24,583 --> 00:11:27,000
Being quints is so complicated.

238
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:29,208
-Hey, Raiha!
-Huh?

239
00:11:29,291 --> 00:11:31,333
You wanna go
and try out the ring toss?

240
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:32,583
Yeah, let's do it!

241
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:34,958
Don't go too far, okay?

242
00:11:35,041 --> 00:11:36,958
Found the yakisoba!

243
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:38,958
Hey, put some spring
in your step!

244
00:11:39,041 --> 00:11:42,750
What's the rush?
And why's she so peppy?

245
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,958
All of you are, actually.

246
00:11:45,041 --> 00:11:47,416
What's the big deal
about the fireworks?

247
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:51,000
Well, it's just, our mom
really loved seeing them.

248
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:55,833
We've always watched the
fireworks together every year.

249
00:11:55,916 --> 00:11:57,583
Even now that she's not here.

250
00:11:58,791 --> 00:12:00,500
It's one of the most
important memories

251
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:01,625
we have of her.

252
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:04,166
♪

253
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:08,000
That's why we keep up
the tradition. It's special.

254
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:09,916
[FUTARO]
I understand that.

255
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,250
No wonder
she's so fixated on it.

256
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:15,416
[ANNOUNCER] Thank you for your
patience, ladies and gentlemen.

257
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,541
The fireworks display
is about to begin!

258
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:19,000
[CROWD cheering]

259
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:22,041
Come on, hurry!
Wait a sec.

260
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:23,083
[MAN]
Let's go!

261
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,500
[NINO]
Where is everyone?

262
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:30,875
Ow! Who stepped on my foot?

263
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:34,125
Yotsuba! Ichika!

264
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:35,916
Itsuki! Miku!

265
00:12:40,541 --> 00:12:41,791
Here, grab on.

266
00:12:45,791 --> 00:12:46,958
[NINO]
Why should I?

267
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:48,750
You won't make it like this.

268
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:51,208
Now, which way is it
to the spot you rented out?

269
00:12:51,291 --> 00:12:53,833
Just so you know,
you aren't invited.

270
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:55,625
Yeah, you said that before.

271
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:59,541
You all need to watch together.

272
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:02,666
♪

273
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,708
[FUTARO]
This way?

274
00:13:13,791 --> 00:13:16,208
[NINO] Yes, it's the roof
of that building.

275
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:20,000
[NINO/FUTARO panting]

276
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:22,291
[NINO]
I'm sure they're already here.

277
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:26,000
[firework whistling]

278
00:13:26,083 --> 00:13:29,083
[explosions]

279
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,666
♪

280
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:38,500
Funny story.
I just realized.

281
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:41,833
I'm the only one who knows
which rooftop we're meeting on.

282
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:44,000
[fireworks continue]

283
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
[ticking]

284
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:52,625
[FUTARO] They say
Tokugawa Ieyasu was the first

285
00:13:52,708 --> 00:13:54,208
to see fireworks in Japan.

286
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:58,250
They first started in China,
then spread to Europe,

287
00:13:58,333 --> 00:13:59,916
then they made it
to Tanegashima.

288
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,916
[NINO]
This is so boring!

289
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,916
Why do I have to share
this great moment with you

290
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,875
and your stupid
fireworks trivia?

291
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,500
Hey, it was your own fault!

292
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:10,583
And none of them are answering
their cell phones, either.

293
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:14,041
I can't believe I finished
all that homework for nothing!

294
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,750
It just isn't fair!

295
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,291
[cell phone buzzing]

296
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:20,958
Hey, Yotsuba!

297
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:22,125
Where are you right now?

298
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:24,583
At the clock tower?

299
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:28,333
Right. Understood.

300
00:14:28,416 --> 00:14:29,916
Stay there.
I'll come and get you.

301
00:14:31,125 --> 00:14:32,833
Okay. Listen!

302
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:34,625
Your little sister
is totally fine.

303
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:36,833
-She's playing with Yotsuba.
-Cool.

304
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:39,416
Well, don't just stand there.
Start dialing!

305
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,791
All right.

306
00:14:45,208 --> 00:14:47,375
Crap, I don't have
anybody's phone number!

307
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:49,625
How completely
useless can you be?

308
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:51,291
-[CROWD chattering]
-[FUTARO] Huh?

309
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,458
Hey. There's Ichika.

310
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,458
[NINO]
You're right, that's her!

311
00:14:59,958 --> 00:15:00,916
[line beeping]

312
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,458
Not working.

313
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:04,583
Is the signal bad?

314
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,750
It's one of the most
important memories

315
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:08,125
that we have of her.

316
00:15:10,791 --> 00:15:13,541
Stay right there.
I'll go find everyone.

317
00:15:18,458 --> 00:15:20,958
It's better than being
stuck here alone with you.

318
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,750
Hmph!

319
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,000
That's for sure.

320
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:27,125
Don't let me down.

321
00:15:27,208 --> 00:15:29,125
Make sure they get up here
in time, okay?

322
00:15:33,375 --> 00:15:35,291
[CROWD oohing]

323
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:40,416
Ichika!

324
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:44,791
[panting]

325
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:47,041
Come with me.

326
00:15:47,125 --> 00:15:48,791
Nino's waiting for you guys
on the rooftop.

327
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:50,208
Let's go.

328
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:55,500
Hey, punk. Get lost.

329
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:57,375
[FUTARO]
Who the heck is this guy?

330
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:01,125
What's your relationship
to Ichika?

331
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:04,750
My what?

332
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:07,916
I guess I'm her... friend?

333
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,625
Teacher? Colleague?

334
00:16:10,708 --> 00:16:12,500
Not sure.

335
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:13,625
We're, uh...

336
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,125
acquaintances!

337
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,166
He's gone.

338
00:16:19,666 --> 00:16:21,541
We're acquaintances!

339
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:24,250
♪

340
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:27,041
Is Ichika
in some kind of trouble?

341
00:16:27,125 --> 00:16:29,250
[MIKU]
Futaro.

342
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:32,208
Ichik-- Oh, Miku.

343
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,708
Thank goodness.

344
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:35,541
I'm surprised you could find me.

345
00:16:37,166 --> 00:16:38,708
You did make a scene.

346
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,166
[FUTARO]
True.

347
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,958
Uh... Come with me.
I have to stop Ichika.

348
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:44,250
-[MIKU] Wait up!
-Uh...

349
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:48,791
Um, I got stepped on.

350
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,666
You go ahead, Futaro.

351
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:54,916
Hop on my back.

352
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:58,416
♪

353
00:17:03,708 --> 00:17:07,041
Okay. Can you see Ichika
from up there?

354
00:17:07,125 --> 00:17:10,625
Ichika? I don't think so.

355
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:14,375
You can't run, though.
I'll slow you down.

356
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:21,500
This isn't working,
you're way too heavy.

357
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,833
♪

358
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:28,250
There, does that feel
any better?

359
00:17:29,916 --> 00:17:31,250
Sure, I guess.

360
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,500
[FUTARO]
Huh? Is she mad at me?

361
00:17:34,875 --> 00:17:37,708
Hey, Raiha, do you want me
to go buy you some takoyaki?

362
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:42,208
Ooh, and they've got yakisoba!
And okonomiyaki back there!

363
00:17:42,291 --> 00:17:44,666
♪

364
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:48,583
Yotsuba. We have
to stay put, remember?

365
00:17:48,666 --> 00:17:50,291
[stomach rumbling]

366
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:51,583
-Uh?
-[giggles]

367
00:17:51,666 --> 00:17:52,916
[BOYS laughing]

368
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,666
Here. You can have this
to hold you over.

369
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:58,916
[chuckles awkwardly]

370
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,583
I owe you one.

371
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:04,250
[MIKU] So, did you say
you ran into Ichika?

372
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,083
[FUTARO]
Yeah.

373
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:08,708
She definitely knew I was there,

374
00:18:08,791 --> 00:18:11,791
but then she took off
with some mustache dude.

375
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:13,083
Anybody you know?

376
00:18:13,166 --> 00:18:14,125
Mm-mm.

377
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:18,375
I think I've seen her
getting out

378
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:20,333
of a mustache guy's car
before, though.

379
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:24,791
[FUTARO]
Seriously?

380
00:18:24,875 --> 00:18:27,458
Okay, that sounds
really suspect.

381
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:29,375
Well, who cares?

382
00:18:29,458 --> 00:18:30,958
Forty minutes left.

383
00:18:31,041 --> 00:18:32,208
What's that girl up to?

384
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:36,166
At this rate,
the fireworks'll be done

385
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:38,583
before I round you guys up!

386
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:41,458
You're being nice,
and it doesn't involve studying.

387
00:18:41,541 --> 00:18:42,875
I can't believe it.

388
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:46,375
Don't be rude.
I'm fully invested in this now.

389
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:51,791
Besides, I saw how hard
you worked to be here.

390
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,583
Think you can walk?

391
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:00,500
[MIKU]
Yeah.

392
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,375
Got a minute?

393
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:04,791
We're taking a survey of people

394
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:07,375
who came to see
the fireworks display.

395
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:10,291
What's the relationship
between you two?

396
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:14,750
What's your relationship
to Ichika?

397
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,750
Oops. There's no need
to ask that question.

398
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:21,375
You two are obviously a couple.

399
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:23,208
-[MIKU/FUTARO gasp]
-Duh.

400
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:26,916
[MIKU] Um, we're actually
not in a relationship.

401
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,625
[WOMAN 1] Really?
You sure look like you are.

402
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:32,916
♪

403
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,666
[MIKU/FUTARO gasp]

404
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:37,500
♪

405
00:19:37,583 --> 00:19:39,416
No, we're not.

406
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,333
It isn't what you think.

407
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:42,958
The two of us are just friends.

408
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:45,291
Yeah, acquaintances, at most!

409
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:50,083
Maybe "schoolmates"
is more fitting.

410
00:19:50,166 --> 00:19:51,500
Mmm.

411
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:54,208
On second thought,
that doesn't quite cover it.

412
00:19:54,291 --> 00:19:56,541
-She's more like my client...
-You know what, never mind.

413
00:19:56,625 --> 00:19:58,875
We're so sorry
for bothering you.

414
00:19:58,958 --> 00:20:00,916
-Futaro.
-Yeah?

415
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:03,666
Hmm?

416
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:06,083
Whoa.

417
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:07,250
What'd I do now?

418
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:11,666
Everything's fine. Never mind.

419
00:20:15,708 --> 00:20:17,833
Futaro. Look.

420
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:22,166
Don't move, okay?
I'll go get her.

421
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,833
-Itsuki!
-Ah!

422
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:29,541
[groans]

423
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:31,541
Oh, great.
It's just you again.

424
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:34,875
At least try to conceal
your disappointment, please.

425
00:20:34,958 --> 00:20:36,791
Miku's resting over there.

426
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:39,208
Let's meet up with her.

427
00:20:39,291 --> 00:20:40,625
[ITSUKI]
Sure.

428
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:42,916
[FUTARO]] Good, now we're
just missing Ichika.

429
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:46,750
Can I ask you something?

430
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:50,125
How would you describe
our relationship?

431
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:53,625
That sure is a creepy question
just to ask me out of the blue.

432
00:20:53,708 --> 00:20:57,625
Hmm. I would say you and I
are basically strangers.

433
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,541
Yeah, we're strangers at best.

434
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:02,041
Did you just say "at best"?

435
00:21:02,125 --> 00:21:04,750
Besides,
you shouldn't need to ask.

436
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,000
If you think very hard
about this,

437
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,166
you should already know
the answer.

438
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:12,375
[fireworks exploding]

439
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:14,875
[CROWD oohing]

440
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:17,875
Anyway, we need to find Ichika.

441
00:21:17,958 --> 00:21:19,416
Where could she have gone?

442
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,958
Hey, nice job.

443
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:26,333
I knew that you'd find
a way to track Itsuki down.

444
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:27,875
Ichi--

445
00:21:29,208 --> 00:21:30,791
[ICHIKA]
This way.

446
00:21:30,875 --> 00:21:32,875
The fireworks are great, huh?

447
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:35,125
[FUTARO]
Hey, what gives?

448
00:21:35,208 --> 00:21:36,833
Aren't you gonna watch
with your sisters?

449
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:39,500
Stop freaking out and follow me!

450
00:21:46,791 --> 00:21:50,208
Huh? Uesugi? Ugh!

451
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,166
[ICHIKA]
Do me a favor.

452
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:59,708
Don't tell the others
what happened earlier.

453
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:02,583
I'm sorry, but...

454
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:05,208
I can't watch the fireworks
with you this year.

455
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:07,708
[fireworks exploding]

456
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:09,708
♪

457
00:22:11,708 --> 00:22:13,583
[BOTH]
Ahh!

458
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,625
♪

459
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:29,958
[ticking]

460
00:24:00,375 --> 00:24:02,083
[QUINTUPLETS]
Quintuplet Trivia!

461
00:24:02,166 --> 00:24:03,916
[FUTARO] I've calculated
the quintuplets'

462
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:04,958
collective bust size.

463
00:24:05,041 --> 00:24:06,541
[ITSUKI]
What's with the robot?

464
00:24:06,625 --> 00:24:09,166
[NINO]
It's 444 centimeters, right?

465
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:11,500
-[buzzer sounds]
-[FUTARO] 441.

466
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:13,041
[QUINTUPLETS]
441?

467
00:24:13,125 --> 00:24:14,666
[ICHIKA]
That's enough math for today!

